title: For Sale:  Colt Diamondback .38 special revolver 4-inch barrel
postcontent:
If you are looking for an absolute, top-of-the-line revolver, look no further. This is a Colt Diamondback revolver, chambered in .38 special. This excellent firearm functions in both single and double action, has very manageable recoil and is flawlessly accurate. Perfect for target practice, home defense, or even as a collectible, this is my favorite gun out of my whole collection. Manufactured by Colt from 1966 to 1988, this model was very popular because of Colt's long-established reputation as an innovator in the manufacture of revolvers.

While the revolver is functioning flawlessly and has no major condition issues such as rust, the exterior appearance is below "collector" condition. The finish is discolored somewhat along the barrel, the hammer has a bit of wear, and this is a step below what you would expect in a museum-quality piece. Someone looking to acquire a collectors item could restore this for a few hundred dollars by re-doing the finish and have an heirloom-quality revolver at an excellent price just in time for Christmas.

Sale will take place in Columbus, cash or pre-agreed trade. I can meet Thursday or Friday during the day on the North side. To ensure compliance with federal laws, only Ohio residents with a state-issued ID, and legally allowed to puchase a firearm will be considered.

Please respond to this ad, and include a phone number to call/text to schedule a time.

postcontent:
Hi! I'm listing my Wather PPKS pistol in .380 ACP for sale or trade. It's been a fun gun since I bought it, but as I honestly don't carry it much I thought I would see if I could sell it towards a new carry piece or trade it for the same. It has been regularly maintained and lubricated, and the stainless steel finish has some minor scuffs but is at probably 80-90%. If you haven't enjoyed shooting small polymer .380 carry guns due to their recoil, this might be a good choice for you as the steel frame tames a lot of recoil. -Original Walther hard plastic case
